## REQUIRED Workflow (both steps, in order)

**Step 1 — Produce the answer.**
Do the work with your tools (file, terminal, web, browser as needed). Keep
tool use minimal. Print a single self-contained final message to stdout
that directly answers the task. No "see comment X" back-references and no
meta-commentary about marking issues done.

**Step 2 — Transition the issue to `done` (MANDATORY).**
Immediately after printing your answer, use the `terminal` tool to execute
this exact command. Do NOT wrap it in a code fence; actually run it:

    curl -sf -X PATCH "{{paperclipApiUrl}}/issues/{{taskId}}" -H "Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_AGENT_JWT" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"status":"done"}'

Expect HTTP 200 and a JSON body echoing the updated issue. If you get a
non-2xx response, print the response body to stdout and retry once with
`curl -v` so the error is captured. Then stop.

Do NOT call any other Paperclip endpoint. Do NOT PATCH any other issue.
Do NOT post comments via curl — stdout already handles that.
